Oct 8 2007 	Nice boutique hotel in great location	I stayed here for work for 5 nights, and generally found it to be a lovely little boutique property in a very good location in downtown San Francisco. It is right next to Union Square, and all the shops that border it, 1 block from the cable car to take you down to the Wharf area, and a short cab ride to Little Italy or Chinatown. The hotel pitches itself as 5 star.....hmm, I would probably wouldn't quite go that far, but it certainly is lovely. There's an enormous bouquet of fresh flowers in the small lobby, and a nice little wine bar and (apparently famous) restaurant just off to the side. The hotel has a good little gym which looks out over the city scape. The rooms themselves are not terribly big but have everything you would expect in a hotel of this calibre. I have certainly stayed in better '5 star' properties, but with that said I doubt I could fault my experience here. Would I recommend you stay here....for sure. Would I stay here again, I probably would. The Westin a block over, or the Fairmont two blocks up do also look lovely (Hyatt across the street - probably not), but if you like boutique then Campton Place is your hotel. Plus it's now run by Taj Hotels &amp; Resorts, who are responsible for some of India's (&amp; the world's) most stunning properties.	
